text: Okwakee Creek is a stream in the U.S. states of Alabama and Mississippi. Okwakee is a name derived from the Choctaw language purported to mean "ridge". Variant names are "Aulkwaukee Creek" and "Oakwalkey Creek". ==References== Category:Rivers of Alabama Category:Bodies of water of Washington County, Alabama Category:Rivers of Mississippi Category:Bodies of water of Greene County, Mississippi
title: Okwakee Creek
